 yards\n'''Top tacklers'''\n* GB \u2013 [[Desmond Bishop]] \u2013 7 tackles, 1 sack\n* ATL \u2013 [[Sean Weatherspoon]] \u2013 11 tackles\n}}\nThe Falcons went home for a week 5 duel with the undefeated Packers.  This would be a rematch of last year's NFC Divisional Round.  With the loss, the Falcons fell to 2\u20133.\n\n====Week 6: vs. Carolina Panthers====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons 90thru02|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Six: Carolina Panthers at Atlanta Falcons&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=October 16\n |time=1:00 p.m. EDT\n |road=Panthers\n |R1=3|R2=7|R3=7|R4=0\n |home='''Falcons'''\n |H1=7|H2=7|H3=0|H4=17\n |stadium=Georgia Dome, Atlanta, Georgia\n |attendance=69,047\n |weather=Played indoors (dome stadium)\n |referee=[[Pete Morelli]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Dick Stockton]] and [[John Lynch (American football)|John Lynch]] |reference=\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*\n'''Second quarter'''\n*\n'''Third quarter'''\n*\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n* CAR \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top rushers'''\n* CAR \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top receivers'''\n* CAR \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top tacklers'''\n* CAR \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n}}\nWith their 3rd-straight win over the Panthers, the Falcons improved to 3\u20133.\n\n====Week 7: at Detroit Lions====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title= Week Seven: Atlanta Falcons at Detroit Lions&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=October 23\n |time=1:00 p.m. EDT\n |road='''Falcons'''\n |R1=10|R2=7|R3=3|R4=3\n |home=Lions\n |H1=3|H2=3|H3=10|H4=0\n |stadium=Ford Field, Detroit, Michigan\n |attendance=63,625\n |weather=Played indoors (dome stadium)\n |referee=[[Bill Leavy]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Sam Rosen (sportscaster)|Sam Rosen]], [[Brian Billick]] and [[Laura Okmin]]\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2011102303/2011/REG7/falco