ons fell to 9\u20136, but were able to clinch a playoff spot due to the Chicago Bears 35\u201321 loss to the Green Bay Packers Sunday night.\n\n====Week 17: vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title= Week Seventeen: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Atlanta Falcons&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=January 1\n |time=4:15 p.m. EST<ref name=\"TB\">{{cite web | author=Adams, Jay | url=http://www.atlantafalcons.com/2011/12/falcons-bucs-game-flexed-to-415-kick/ | title=Falcons-Bucs Game 'Flexed' to 4:15 Kick | work=atlantafalcons.com | accessdate=2011-12-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107194333/http://www.atlantafalcons.com/2011/12/falcons-bucs-game-flexed-to-415-kick/ | archive-date=2012-01-07 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n |road=Buccaneers\n |R1=0|R2=7|R3=11|R4=6\n |home='''Falcons'''\n |H1=21|H2=21|H3=0|H4=3\n |stadium=Georgia Dome, Atlanta, Georgia\n |attendance=68,167\n |weather=Played indoors (dome stadium)\n |referee=[[Scott Green (American football official)|Scott Green]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers= [[Dick Stockton]] & [[John Lynch (American football)|John Lynch]]\n |reference=\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*\n'''Second quarter'''\n*\n'''Third quarter'''\n*\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n* TB \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top rushers'''\n* TB \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top receivers'''\n* TB \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top tacklers'''\n* TB \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n}}\n\nWith the win, the Falcons finished the season at 10\u20136 and captured the NFC's #5 seed.\n\n===Standings===\n{{2011 NFC South standings}}\n\n==Postseason==\n{{main|2011\u201312 NFL playoffs}}\n===Schedule===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \"align=center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Playoff round !! rowspan=\"2\" | Date !! rowspan=\"2\" | Kickoff !! rowspan=\"2\" | Opponent (seed) !! colspan=\"2\" | Results !! rowspan=\"2\" | Game site !! rowspan=\"2\" | TV !! rowspan=\"2\" | NFL.com<br>recap\n|-\n! Final score !! Team record\n|- style=\"background:#fcc\"\n! Wild Card\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| January 8, 2012\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 1:00&nbsp;p.m. [[North American Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| at [[2011 New York Giants season|New York Giants]] (4)\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| '''L''' 2\u201324\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| 0\u20131\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[MetLife Stadium]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[NFL on Fox|Fox]]\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"| [http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2012010801/2011/POST18/falcons@giants Recap]\n|}\n\n===Game summaries===\n====NFC Wild Card Playoff Game: at #4 New York Giants====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=NFC Wild Card Playoff Game: Atlanta Falcons at New York Giants&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=January 8, 2012\n |time=1:00 p.m. [[North American Eastern Time Zone|EST]]\n |road=Falcons\n |R1=0|R2=2|R3=0|R4=0\n |home='''Giants'''\n |H1=0|H2=7|H3=10|H4=7\n |stadium=[[MetLife Stadium]], [[East Rutherford, New Jersey]]\n |attendance=79,909\n |weather={{convert|44|\u00b0F|\u00b0C|1}}, Partly Cloudy\n |referee=[[Carl Cheffers]]\n |TV=[[NFL on Fox|Fox]]\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Joe Buck]], [[Troy Aikman]] and [[Pam Oliver]]\n |reference=\n |scoring=\n'''Second quarter'''\n* ATL Intentional Grounding Penalty on [[Eli Manning]] in end zone for a Safety (13:44)\n* NYG [[Hakeem Nicks]] 4-yard pass from [[Eli Manning]] ([[Lawrence Tynes]] kick) (13\u201385, 7:32)\n'''Third quarter'''\n* NYG [[Lawrence Tynes]] 22-yard field goal (11\u201372, 4:47)\n* NYG [[Hakeem Nicks]] 72-yard pass from [[Eli Manning]] ([[Lawrence Tynes]] kick) (3\u201379, 1:32)\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n* NYG [[Mario Manningham]] 27-yard pass from [[Eli Manning]] ([[Lawrence Tynes]] kick) (10\u201385, 5:38)\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n* ATL \u2013\n* NYG \u2013\n'''Top rushers'''\n* ATL \u2013\n* NYG \u2013\n'''Top receivers'''\n* ATL \u2013\n* NYG \u2013\n'''Top tacklers'''\n* ATL \u2013\n* NYG \u2013\n}}\nThe Falcons lost their [[NFL Wild card|Wild Card]] round playoff game to the [[2011 New York Giants season|New York Giants]] on January 8, 2012, by a score of 24\u20132. It is the first time in NFL playoff history that a team has scored exactly two points. The previous NFL team to score only a safety in a game was [[1993 Cincinnati Bengals season|the 1993 Cincinnati Bengals]] in Week 15 against [[1993 New England Patriots season|the New England Patriots]].\n\n==Staff==\n{| class=\"toccolours\" style=\"text-align: left;\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"7\" style=\"background:#bd0d18; color:white; text-align: center; border:2px solid black;\"|'''Atlanta Falcons 2011 staff'''\n|-\n|colspan=7 align=\"right\" |\n|-\n|valign=\"top\"|\n| style=\"font-size: 95%;\" valign=\"top\" | '''Front Office'''\n*Owner \u2013 [[Arthur Blank]]\n*President/CEO \u2013 [[Rich McKay]]\n*General Manager \u2013 [[Thomas Dimitroff]]\n*Director of Football Administration \u2013 [[Nick Polk]]\n*Director of Player Personnel \u2013 [[Les Snead]]\n*Assistant Director of Player Personnel \u2013 [[Lionel Vital]]\n*Director of College Scouting \u2013 [[Dave Caldwell (American football)|Dave Caldwell]]\n\n'''Head Coaches'''\n*Head Coach \u2013 [[Mike Smith (American football coach)|Mike Smith]]\n\n'''Offensive Coaches'''\n*Offensive Coordinator \u2013 [[Mike Mularkey]]\n*Quarterbacks \u2013 [[Bob Bratkowski]]\n*Running Backs \u2013 [[Gerald Brown (American football)|Gerald Brown]]\n*Wide Receivers \u2013 [[Terry Robiskie]]\n*Tight Ends \u2013 [[Chris Scelfo]]\n*Offensive Line \u2013 [[Paul Boudreau|Paul T Boudreau]]\n*Assistant Offensive Line \u2013 [[Paul Dunn (coach)|Paul Dunn]]\n*Offensive Assistant \u2013 [[Glenn Thomas (American football)|Glenn Thomas]]\n*Assistant to the Head Coach/Offense \u2013 [[Andrew Weidinger]]\n\n|width=\"35\"|&nbsp;\n|valign=\"top\"|\n| style=\"font-size: 95%