nta]]\n[[Category:Atlanta Falcons seasons]]\n[[Category:2011 in sports in Georgia (U.S. state)]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox NFL season\n| team = Atlanta Falcons\n| year = 2011\n| record = 10\u20136 <!--Do not add zero ties-->\n| division_place = 2nd [[NFC South]]\n| coach = [[Mike Smith (American football coach)|Mike Smith]]\n| general manager = [[Thomas Dimitroff]]\n| owner = [[Arthur Blank]]\n| stadium = [[Georgia Dome]]\n| playoffs = Lost  [[2011\u201312 NFL Playoffs|Wild Card Playoffs]] (at [[2011 New York Giants season|Giants]]) 2\u201324\n| pro bowlers = [[Tony Gonzalez]], TE, [[Roddy White]], WR\n| colors = Red, Black, White, Silver\n {{Color box|#bd0d18}} {{Color box|black}} {{Color box|white}} {{Color box|#dce0e5}}\n| shortnavlink    = Falcons seasons\n}}\nThe '''{{nfly|2011}} [[List of Atlanta Falcons seasons|Atlanta Falcons season]]''' was the franchise's 46th season in the [[National Football League]] and the fourth under head coach [[Mike Smith (American football coach)|Mike Smith]].\n\nFinishing the regular season 10\u20136, the Falcons clinched the #5 seed in the [[2011-12 NFL Playoffs|playoffs]].  Atlanta\u2019s season ended quickly as they lost 24\u20132 to [[Eli Manning]] and [[2011 New York Giants season|the New York Giants]] in the opening round. The Giants would go on to defeat [[Tom Brady]] and [[2011 New England Patriots season|the New England Patriots]] in the Super Bowl.\n\nThis is also the first time the franchise clinched consecutive playoff berths, and the first time it won ten or more games in consecutive seasons.\n{{TOClimit|3}}\n\n==Offseason==\n===Signings===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%; text-align: left;\"\n|-\n! Pos. !! Player !! 2010 Team !! Contract\n|-\n| DE || [[Ray Edwards (American football)|Ray Edwards]] || [[Minnesota Vikings]] || 5 years, $27.5 million\n|-\n| OLB || [[Stephen Nicholas]] || [[Atlanta Falcons]] || 5 years, $17.5 million\n|-\n| K || [[Matt Bryant]] || [[Atlanta Falcons]] || 4 years, $10.7 million\n|-\n|}\n\n===Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%; text-align: left;\"\n|-\n! Pos. !! Player !! 2011 Team \n|-\n| WR ||[[Michael Jenkins (wide receiver)|Michael Jenkins]] || [[Minnesota Vikings]]\n|-\n| DE || [[Jamaal Anderson]] || [[Indianapolis Colts]]\n|-\n|-\n| WR || [[Brian Finneran]] || \n|-\n|}\n\n===2011 NFL Draft===\n{{main|2011 NFL Draft}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size: 95%;\"\n|-\n! Round !! Selection !! Player !! Position !! College\n|-\n! 1 || 6\n| [[Julio Jones]] || [[Wide Receiver]] || [[University of Alabama|Alabama]] \n|-\n! 3 || 91\n| [[Akeem Dent]] || [[Inside Linebacker]] || [[University of Georgia|Georgia]]\n|-\n! 5 || 158\n|  [[Jacquizz Rogers]]  || [[Running Back]] || [[Oregon State]]\n|-\n! 6 || 192\n| [[Matt Bosher]] || [[Punter (football)|Punter]] || [[Miami (FL)]]\n|-\n! 7 || 210 {{ref|Chris Houston trade|[a]}}\n|[[Andrew Jackson (offensive guard)|Andrew Jackson]] || [[Offensive Guard]] || [[Fresno State]]\n\n|-\n! 7 || 230 {{ref|Quinn Ojinnaka trade|[b]}}\n| [[Cliff Matthews (American football)|Cliff Matthews]] || [[Defensive End]] || [[South Carolina]]\n|}\n:<sup>{{note|Chris Houston trade|[a]}}</sup> The Falcons acquired this seventh-round selection and a [[2010 NFL Draft|2010]] sixth-round selection in a trade that sent [[Cornerback|CB]] [[Chris Houston (American football)|Chris Houston]] to the [[Detroit Lions]].\n:<sup>{{note|Quinn Ojinnaka trade|[b]}}</sup> The Falcons acquired this seventh-round selection in a trade that sent [[Offensive tackle|T]] [[Quinn Ojinnaka]] to the [[New England Patriots]].\n\n==Preseason==\n===Schedule===\nThe Falcons' preseason schedule was announced on April 12, 2011.\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"align=center\"\n|-\n! Week !! Date !! Opponent !! Result !! Record !! Game site !! NFL.com<br>recap\n|- style=\"background:#fcc\"\n! 1\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| August 12\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"| [[2011 Miami Dolphins season|Miami Dolphins]]\n|style=\