] \u2013 5 receptions, 140 yards, 1 TD\n* ATL \u2013 [[Tony Gonzalez]] \u2013 6 receptions, 60 yards\n'''Top tacklers'''\n* GB \u2013 [[Desmond Bishop]] \u2013 7 tackles, 1 sack\n* ATL \u2013 [[Sean Weatherspoon]] \u2013 11 tackles\n}}\nThe Falcons went home for a week 5 duel with the undefeated Packers.  This would be a rematch of last year's NFC Divisional Round.  With the loss, the Falcons fell to 2\u20133.\n\n====Week 6: vs. Carolina Panthers====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons 90thru02|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Six: Carolina Panthers at Atlanta Falcons&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=October 16\n |time=1:00 p.m. EDT\n |road=Panthers\n |R1=3|R2=7|R3=7|R4=0\n |home='''Falcons'''\n |H1=7|H2=7|H3=0|H4=17\n |stadium=Georgia Dome, Atlanta, Georgia\n |attendance=69,047\n |weather=Played indoors (dome stadium)\n |referee=[[Pete Morelli]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Dick Stockton]] and [[John Lynch (American football)|John Lynch]] |reference=\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*\n'''Second quarter'''\n*\n'''Third quarter'''\n*\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n* CAR \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top rushers'''\n* CAR \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top receivers'''\n* CAR \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top tacklers'''\n* CAR \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n}}\nWith their 3rd-straight win over the Panthers, the Falcons improved to 3\u20133.\n\n====Week 7: at Detroit Lions====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title= Week Seven: Atlanta Falcons at Detroit Lions&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=October 23\n |time=1:00 p.m. EDT\n |road='''Falcons'''\n |R1=10|R2=7|R3=3|R4=3\n |home=Lions\n |H1=3|H2=3|H3=10|H4=0\n |stadium=Ford Field, Detroit, Michigan\n |attendance=63,625\n |weather=Played indoors (dome stadium)\n |referee=[[Bill Leavy]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Sam Rosen (sportscaster)|Sam Rosen]], [[Brian Billick]] and [[Laura Okmin]]\n |reference=[http://www.nfl.com/gamecenter/2011102303/2011/REG7/falcons@lions Recap]<br>[http://www.nfl.com/liveupdate/gamecenter/55256/DET_Gamebook.pdf Gamebook]\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*DET \u2013 [[Jason Hanson]] 43-yard field goal, ''Lions 3\u20130,'' '''''Drive: 4 plays, \u221210 yards, 1:47.'''''\n*ATL \u2013 Matt Bryant 23-yard field goal, ''Tied 3\u20133,'' '''''Drive: 7 plays, 21 yards, 3:03.'''''\n*ATL \u2013 Matt Ryan 1-yard run (Matt Bryant kick), ''Falcons 10\u20133,'' '''''5 plays, 28 yards, 2:46.'''''\n'''Second quarter'''\n*DET \u2013 Jason Hanson 38-yard field goal, ''Falcons 10\u20136,'' '''''Drive: 9 plays, 50 yards, 4:12.'''''\n*ATL \u2013 Roddy White 18-yard pass from Matt Ryan (Matt Bryant kick), ''Falcons 17\u20136,'' '''''Drive: 7 plays, 81 yards, 3:05'''''\n'''Third quarter'''\n*DET \u2013 Jason Hanson 29-yard field goal, ''Falcons 17\u20139,'' '''''Drive: 6 plays, 35 yards, 2:25.'''''\n*ATL \u2013 Matt Bryant 47 yard, ''Falcons 20\u20139,'' '''''Drive: 7 plays, 51 yards, 2;33.'''''\n*DET \u2013 [[Calvin Johnson (American football)|Calvin Johnson]] 57-yard pass from Matthew Stafford (Jason Hanson kick), ''Falcons 20\u201316,'' '''''Drive: 6 plays, 84 yards, 3:07.'''''\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n*ATL \u2013 Matt Bryant 40-yard field goal, ''Falcons 23\u201316,'' '''''Drive: 9 plays, 25 yards, 4:42.'''''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n* ATL \u2013 Matt Ryan \u2013 20/34, 218 yards, 1 touchdown, 2 interceptions\n* DET \u2013 [[Matthew Stafford]] \u2013 15/32, 183 yards, 1 touchdown\n'''Top rushers'''\n* ATL \u2013 Michael Turner \u2013 27 carries, 122 yards\n* DET \u2013 [[Maurice Morris]] \u2013 9 carries, 50 yards\n'''Top receivers'''\n* ATL \u2013 Tony Gonzalez \u2013 5 receptions, 62 yards\n* DET \u2013 Calvin Johnson \u2013 5 receptions, 115 yards, 1 touchdown\n'''Top tacklers'''\n* ATL \u2013 Curtis Lofton \u2013 5 tackles, 5 assists\n* DET \u2013 [[DeAndre Levy]] \u2013 6 tackles, 5 assists\n}}\nWith the win, the Falcons went into their bye week at 4\u20133.\n\n====Week 9: at Indianapolis Colts====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title= Week Nine: Atlanta Falcons at Indianapolis Colts&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=November 6\n |time=1:00 p.m. EST\n |road='''Falcons'''\n |R1=14|R2=7|R3=7|R4=3\n |home=Colts\n |H1=0|H2=7|H3=0|H4=0\n |stadium=[[Lucas Oil Stadium]], [[Indianapolis, Indiana]]\n |attendance=65,218\n |weather={{convert|57|\u00b0F|\u00b0C|1|disp=or}} (sunny, retractable roof open)\n |referee=[[Mike Carey (American football)|Mike Carey]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=[[Ron Pitts]], [[Jim L. Mora|Jim Mora, Jr.]]\n |reference={{citation needed|date=December 2011}}\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*\n'''Second quarter'''\n*\n'''Third quarter'''\n*\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n* ATL \u2013\n* IND \u2013\n'''Top rushers'''\n* ATL \u2013\n* IND \u2013\n'''Top receivers'''\n* ATL \u2013\n* IND \u2013\n'''Top tacklers'''\n* ATL \u2013\n* IND \u2013\n}}\nWith the win, the Falcons improved to 5\u20133 and went 2\u201313 overall against the Colts.\n\n====Week 10: vs. New Orleans Saints====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons 90thru02|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title=Week Ten: New Orleans Saints at Atlanta Falcons&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=November 13\n |time=1:00 p.m. EST\n |road='''Saints'''\n |R1=3|R2=7|R3=7|R4=6|R5=3\n |home=Falcons\n |H1=3|H2=3|H3=7|H4=10|H5=0\n |stadium=Georgia Dome, Atlanta, Georgia\n |attendance=70,359\n |weather=Played indoors (dome stadium)\n |referee=[[Terry McAulay]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers=Kenny Albert, Daryl Johnston and Tony Siragusa\n |reference={{citation needed|date=December 2011}}\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n* ATL \u2013 [[Matt Bryant|M.Bryant]] 36 yd. Field Goal ''Falcons 3\u20130. '''Drive: 16 plays, 61 yards, 8:40.'''''\n* NO \u2013 [[John Kasa