assist\n* ATL \u2013 [[Thomas DeCoud]] \u2013 7 tackles, 3 assist\n}}\nWith the loss, the Falcons fell to 9\u20136, but were able to clinch a playoff spot due to the Chicago Bears 35\u201321 loss to the Green Bay Packers Sunday night.\n\n====Week 17: vs. Tampa Bay Buccaneers====\n{{Americanfootballbox\n |titlestyle={{NFLPrimaryStyle|Atlanta Falcons|border=2}};text-align:center;\n |state=autocollapse\n |title= Week Seventeen: Tampa Bay Buccaneers at Atlanta Falcons&nbsp;\u2013 Game summary\n |date=January 1\n |time=4:15 p.m. EST<ref name=\"TB\">{{cite web | author=Adams, Jay | url=http://www.atlantafalcons.com/2011/12/falcons-bucs-game-flexed-to-415-kick/ | title=Falcons-Bucs Game 'Flexed' to 4:15 Kick | work=atlantafalcons.com | accessdate=2011-12-24 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120107194333/http://www.atlantafalcons.com/2011/12/falcons-bucs-game-flexed-to-415-kick/ | archive-date=2012-01-07 | url-status=dead }}</ref>\n |road=Buccaneers\n |R1=0|R2=7|R3=11|R4=6\n |home='''Falcons'''\n |H1=21|H2=21|H3=0|H4=3\n |stadium=Georgia Dome, Atlanta, Georgia\n |attendance=68,167\n |weather=Played indoors (dome stadium)\n |referee=[[Scott Green (American football official)|Scott Green]]\n |TV=Fox\n |TVAnnouncers= [[Dick Stockton]] & [[John Lynch (American football)|John Lynch]]\n |reference=\n |scoring=\n'''First quarter'''\n*\n'''Second quarter'''\n*\n'''Third quarter'''\n*\n'''Fourth quarter'''\n |stats=\n'''Top passers'''\n* TB \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top rushers'''\n* TB \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top receivers'''\n* TB \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n'''Top tacklers'''\n* TB \u2013\n* ATL \u2013\n}}\n\nWith the win, the Falcons finished the season at 10\u20136 and captured the NFC's #5 seed.\n\n===Standings===\n{{2011 NFC South standings}}\n\n==Postseason==\n{{main|2011\u201312 NFL playoffs}}\n===Schedule===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" \"align=center\"\n|-\n! rowspan=\"2\" | Playoff round !! rowspan=\"2\" | Date !! rowspan=\"2\" | Kickoff !! rowspan=\"2\" | Opponent (seed)